title: SyntaxError: Missing Closing Parenthesis in index.js
root_cause_summary: The build failure is caused by a syntax error in the index.js file. Specifically, there is a missing closing parenthesis after the 'Hello there' string in the res.send() function call on line 6.
root_cause_detailed: The JavaScript interpreter encountered a SyntaxError while parsing the index.js file. This error occurs when the syntax of the code violates the rules of the JavaScript language. In this case, the error message 'missing ) after argument list' indicates that a function call is missing its closing parenthesis. The error is located on line 6 of index.js, where the res.send() function is called with the 'Hello there' argument.

fix_suggestions.title: Add missing closing parenthesis in index.js
fix_suggestions.description: This fix directly addresses the syntax error by adding the missing closing parenthesis to the res.send() function call.
implementation_steps: Step 2: Locate the res.send() function call on line 6
Step 3: Add a closing parenthesis after the 'Hello there' string
Step 4: Save the file and commit the changes

fix_suggestions.title: Use a JavaScript linter to check for syntax errors
fix_suggestions.description: Running a JavaScript linter will help identify and fix not only this syntax error but also any other potential issues in the codebase.
implementation_steps: Step 1: Install a JavaScript linter (e.g., ESLint) if not already present
Step 2: Run the linter on the project files
Step 3: Review and fix any syntax errors or warnings reported by the linter
Step 4: Commit the changes and re-run the CI/CD pipeline
fix_suggestions.source: Web research on JavaScript syntax errors

fix_suggestions.title: Review recent changes to index.js
fix_suggestions.description: Examining recent commits to index.js may reveal how the syntax error was introduced and help prevent similar issues in the future.
implementation_steps: Step 1: Check the git log for recent commits affecting index.js
Step 2: Review the changes made in those commits
Step 3: Identify the commit that introduced the syntax error
Step 4: Understand why the error was introduced and update coding practices if necessary
fix_suggestions.source: Best practices for debugging CI/CD failures

research_summary: Web research confirms that the 'SyntaxError: missing ) after argument list' is a common JavaScript error caused by incomplete function calls. It also highlights the importance of proper syntax in CI/CD environments and suggests using linters to catch such errors early.
